  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a prospective research study talking place at University hospital of Dijon and
      requiring the inclusion of 20 healthy subjects, 10 patients with unilateral cochlear implants
      and 10 patients with bilateral cochlear implants to carry out:

        -  an audio-vestibular examination,

        -  a videonystagmoscopic study,

        -  a posturography study and

        -  a movement study. The aim of the study is to evaluate the impact of binaural audition on
           postural performance and orientation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
